[b]Market Tradability Engine[/b] is a market-quality and no-trade filter — it classifies the current market into one of eight states instead of generating directional entries, so it can gate whether the market is actually worth trading right now.

[b]What it does[/b]

Four weighted scores are computed every bar: [b]Tradability[/b] (0-100, blending efficiency ratio, ADX, baseline slope, directional consistency, baseline cleanliness, candle quality, volatility expansion and participation), [b]Balance[/b] (0-100), [b]Compression[/b] (0-100) and [b]Direction[/b] (-100 to +100). ADX's contribution to Tradability is gated by the current efficiency ratio, so a still-elevated ADX from a finished impulse can't prop up the score once price has gone quiet. These drive an eight-state market machine with disagreement-streak confirmation and minimum-duration hysteresis to avoid state flicker:

[list]
[*][b]NO TRADE[/b] — inefficient, noisy, directionless market
[*][b]BALANCE[/b] — established sideways auction with stable boundaries
[*][b]COMPRESSION[/b] — volatility contracts inside balance
[*][b]READY[/b] — compression plus directional pressure near a range boundary
[*][b]BREAKOUT[/b] — confirmed departure from the balance area
[*][b]TREND[/b] — efficient directional expansion
[*][b]AFTERMATH[/b] — a recent directional impulse has gone quiet, detected via a dual-window (fast/slow) efficiency ratio, so the pause isn't mislabeled as a fresh balance
[*][b]EXHAUSTION[/b] — extended trend with declining quality
[/list]

[b]Visuals[/b]

[list]
[*]Balance boundary lines, midline and continuous state-colored background
[*]Transition markers for Ready, Breakout, No-Trade entry, Aftermath and Exhaustion
[*]Dashboard with score breakdown, live candidate state and a plain-language action hint per state
[*]Presets that resolve all lookback lengths at once, or fully custom parameters
[/list]

[b]Calibration logging[/b]

An off-by-default toggle writes structured Pine Log lines (config snapshot, per-bar raw scores, state-transition context) meant for exporting to CSV and calibrating thresholds offline against score distributions, rather than by eye on a single chart.

[b]Scope[/b]

This script does not generate unconditional buy/sell signals. The Ready and Breakout markers identify a market-state transition, not a complete trade setup — they are meant to gate or contextualize signals from a separate entry indicator.

